
[1]backstays

   BACK'STAYS, n. [back and stay.]

   Long ropes or stays extending from the top-mast heads to both sides of
   a ship, to assist the shrouds in supporting the mast, when strained by
   a weight of sail, and prevent it from giving way and falling overboard.
